        <details class="leetcode-insight-guide">
          <summary>{isZh ? "猜你想练的排序规则" : "How suggested practice is ranked"}</summary>
          <div>
            {
              isZh ? (
                <>
                  <p>
                    “猜你想练”按 0 到 100 的练习调度分排序。分数越高，越值得现在
                    打开。它只使用当前浏览器记录到的本页状态、运行和提交行为，
                    不读取力扣历史提交。
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    只要还有 Hot100 题没有完整 AC，这类题会先于其他候选进入推荐队列；
                    在 Hot100 未 AC 候选内部，再继续按练习调度分排序。
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    公式可以理解为：
                    <code>到期复习 + 薄弱程度 + 题目价值 + 当前适配 - 疲劳惩罚</code>，
                    最后截断到 0 到 100。
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    浮层里的“开始推荐流”会把“猜你想练”保持为沉浸流：先打开当前
                    第一推荐；之后只有完整提交 AC 才会重新计算并跳到下一道推荐题。
                    它不是页面下一题，运行样例通过不会跳。
                  </p>
                  <ol>
                    <li>
                      <strong>到期复习：</strong>页面会估计每题的本地稳定度和可回忆率。
                      完整 AC、连续 AC、样例通过和“熟练”会提高稳定度；失败、耗时偏慢
                      和“需思考”会降低稳定度。距离上次 AC 越久，可回忆率越低。
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>薄弱程度：</strong>没有完整 AC、提交失败、样例失败、
                      每 10 行耗时偏慢和“需思考”会提高分数；近期连续 AC、样例通过
                      和“熟练”会降低分数。
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>题目价值：</strong>Top888 频率、Hot100、字节企业题库、
                      最近字节 bucket、核心标签覆盖和相关题网络会提高分数，避免
                      低频冷门题只因为“不会”长期压过高频核心题。
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>当前适配：</strong>如果当前打开了一题，共享标签、相关题
                      和难度邻近会提高推荐分，让下一题更像同路线迁移或合理进阶。
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>疲劳惩罚：</strong>今天已经 AC、当前 session 已经 AC、
                      或与今天已练标签高度重复的题会降分，避免推荐流卡在同一类题里。
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>冷启动：</strong>没有本地提交记录的题也可以被推荐，但主要
                      依赖题目价值、人工状态和未建立稳定度的风险。
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                  <p>
                    分数相同时，优先看到期复习、薄弱程度、题目价值、提交失败、
                    样例失败、计分速度和 AC 次数，最后再用力扣频率排序。这个排序是
                    启发式建议，不是能力证明。
                  </p>
                </>
              ) : (
                <>
                  <p>
                    Suggested practice is ranked by a 0 to 100 scheduling score.
                    Higher scores are better candidates to open now. The score uses
                    only local page state, run activity, and submission activity
                    from this browser, not historical LeetCode submissions.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    As long as any Hot100 problem is missing a full Accepted submit,
                    those Hot100 candidates are recommended before other problems;
                    within that group, the scheduling score still decides the order.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    Read the formula as:
                    <code>review due-ness + weakness + problem value + current fit - fatigue penalty</code>,
                    clamped to 0 to 100.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    "Start suggested flow" holds Suggested practice as the
                    immersive route: it opens the current top recommendation first,
                    then only a full Accepted submit recomputes and opens the next
                    recommendation. It is not the next visible row, and passing
                    sample runs do not advance it.
                  </p>
                  <ol>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Review due-ness:</strong> the page estimates local
                      stability and retrievability. Accepted submissions, Accepted
                      streaks, passed samples, and mastered state raise stability;
                      failures, slow normalized time, and review state lower it.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Weakness:</strong> missing full Accepted evidence,
                      submit failures, sample failures, slow time per 10 lines, and
                      review state raise the score; recent Accepted streaks, passed
                      samples, and mastered state lower it.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Problem value:</strong> Top888 frequency, Hot100,
                      ByteDance buckets, core tag coverage, and related-problem
                      centrality raise the score.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Current fit:</strong> when a problem is open, shared
                      tags, related links, and nearby difficulty prefer same-route
                      transfer or reasonable progression.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Fatigue penalty:</strong> problems Accepted today,
                      Accepted in the current session, or heavily overlapping with
                      tags practiced today are lowered.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Cold start:</strong> problems without local submission
                      stats can still be recommended through value, manual state,
                      and the risk of not having stable memory yet.
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                  <p>
                    Ties prefer review due-ness, weakness, value, submit failures,
                    sample failures, scoring speed, Accepted count, and then
                    LeetCode frequency. This ranking is a heuristic suggestion, not
                    proof of ability.
                  </p>
                </>
              )
            }
          </div>
        </details>

